## 1. Definition
An **Embedding Model** converts text, images, or other data into **numerical vectors** (lists of numbers).  
These vectors capture **semantic meaning**, so similar content has vectors close to each other in vector space.

---

## 2. Why Use Embeddings?
- Machines canâ€™t understand raw text; embeddings turn it into math.  
- Enables:
  - **Semantic search** â†’ Find meaning-based matches, not just keywords.
  - **Clustering** â†’ Group related content.
  - **RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)** â†’ Let LLMs use your own data.

